From an Si attitude, one seeks stabilization rather than stimulation: well aware that $100 in the bank might be worth much less depending on other conditions, you look for ways to set things up so that you ''can'' safely depend on that fact holding its meaning despite changing conditions.  You learn to anticipate unexpected consequences (mostly bad ones, mostly learned from concrete experience with failures) and plan or design to prevent them from coming about.
@@ version 6; date 2003.12.28.3.7.52; author Ben Kovitz;
